@NODE Requirements "Whats needed to run DosWedge"

Requirements
************

	The following are required for DosWedge to run:

	  o @{" matrix.library " LINK MxLib} version 23.1103 or higher

	  o @{" MultiuserFileSystem " LINK MUFS} version 1.5 or higher

	  o Kickstart 37 or higher

@ENDNODE




@NODE Introduction

Introduction
************

	Dos Wedge is a patch for AmigaDOS to give a *IX like directory access,
	implementing . .. / ~ and ~name through several dos patches.


	The following AmigaDOS functions are patched:

	    AssignLate()
	    AssignPath()
	    CreateDir()
	    DeleteFile()
	    IsFileSystem()
	    LoadSeg()
	    Lock()
	    MakeLink()
	    MatchFirst()
	    NewLoadSeg()
	    Open()
	    Rename()
	    SetComment()
	    SetCurrentDirName()
	    SetFileDate()
	    SetProtection()

	V39 Additional patches:

	    SetOwner()

@ENDNODE





@NODE Installation

Installation
************

	Use the installer.

@ENDNODE





@NODE Useage "How to use Dos Wedge"

How To Use Dos Wedge
********************

	When Dos Wedge is enabled you may access directories in a slightly
	different manner than usual. The following are the standard patches
	Dos Wedge will install:

	  .         = the current directory

	  ..        = the parent directory

	  ~         = the current users home directory "$Home"

	  ~userid   = a specific users home directory, this is only available
	              if you are using the @{" MultiUserFileSystem " LINK MUFS}.


	You must specify SLASHPATCH=TRUE (tooltype or cli argument) to enable the
	following:

	  /name/    = this is converted to  "name:"

	  /         = this is equivalent to ":"


	Removal
	*******

	Dos Wedge may be removed by running the "DosWedge" program again or by
	using the commodities exchange.

@ENDNODE





